originalText.text:
Dear A&E Networks,

I just finished watching the "Sons of Liberty" on The History Channel.

Excellent Work. Thank You.

Honestly, I was nervous before it aired. But this production was wonderful.
Writing, Filming, Casting, "Look", etc. And Balance.

Balanced the blunt and bloody, without revelry. The passion and patriotism, with intelligence and thought. And somehow balanced critical events over a 6-7 year period, while keeping the feeling very "now".

Excellence throughout. Wow.

I don't believe that our schools do enough to educate our youth on the foundations of their country. And how to run it. Before it runs us.

Please re-broadcast this film, often. And support other productions of the same quality.

I am 53 years old. A mother of two. Enjoyed the musical film "1776" as an elementary school student. (And several times since.) Feel great civic responsibility, and try to be informed.

And I learned SO MUCH in this "Sons of Liberty" film !!!!
Thank you. Thank you. Thank you.

Toni Rayner
Austin, TX

cc: sponsor Sam Adams Brewing Co

Longmire was the best new type western show in a long time.  You took off The Glades too and it was more worth watching than a lot of shows.  We have shows with firemen, lawyers, crime scene investigators, and city cops but nothing like Longmire.  Keep him on so we can enjoy our few nights of TV

Have observed there to be a hack writer of a show which seems to enjoy bashing religion instead of creating good, quality entertainment. Unsure why the A&E Network allows this.

Per one main star on one of their shows, there is no vetting of would-be sour grapes which I cannot fathom them speak anything but untruths. Please base your shows on facts regarding important subjects, not fiction.

I no longer am interested in the network for this lack of care and quality work.
